# WebDriver Methods in Selenium
1️⃣ What is WebDriver in Selenium?
WebDriver is the main component of selenium used to control web browsers using code.
Using WebDriver we can:
    1. Open web pages
    2. Click buttons
    3. Enter text
    4. Navigate between pages
    5. Execute Javascript
    6. Handle cookies
    7. Take Screenshots
    8. Perform automated testing
WebDriver acts as an interface between python code and the browser

2️⃣ Creating a WebDriver Object
Before using selenium , we must create a WebDriver object.
Each browser has its own WebDriver class.
Example:
    1. Chrome -> webdriver.Chrome()
    2. FireFox -> webdriver.FireFox()
    3. Edge -> webdriver.Ddge()

Example : FireFox WebDriver
    from selenium import WebDriver

    # create WebDriver Object
    driver=WebDriver.FireFox()

    Here:
        1. WebDriver -> Selenium module
        2. driver -> controls the browser

3️⃣ Arguments for WebDriver
When starting WebDriver , we can pass optional arguments to customize browser behavior.
Argument & Description
----------------------
1. desired_capabilities -> Dictionary used to request browser capabilities
2. browser_profile -> Firefox profile configuration
3. proxy -> Used to configure proxy settings
4. keep_alive -> Keeps HTTP connection alive (default False)
5. file_detector -> Used for detecting file uploads
6. options -> Browser configuration like headless mode , window size etc..

4️⃣ How to Use WebDriver
After creating the driver, we can control the browser.
    Example:
        from selenium import webdriver

        driver = webdriver.Firefox()

        # Open webpage
        driver.get("https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/")

        # Execute JavaScript
        script = "alert('Hello from Selenium!')"
        driver.execute_script(script)
    
        This code:

            1. Opens Firefox
            2. Opens the website
            3. Shows a JavaScript alert

5️⃣ WebDriver Methods
WebDriver provides many methods to control the browser.
They are categorized into different groups.

6️⃣ Navigation Methods
Used to navigate between web pages.
    Method & Description
    ---------------------
    1. get(url) -> Opens the specified url
    2. back() -> Goes back to previous page
    3. forward() -> Goes forward in history
    4. refresh() -> Refreshes current page
    5. set_page_load_timeout(time) -> Sets max time for page load

    Example:
        driver.get("https://google.com")
        driver.back()
        driver.forward()
        driver.refresh()
    
7️⃣ Window Management Methods
Used to contro browser window size and position.
    Method & Description
    --------------------
    1. maximize_window() -> Maximizes browser
    2. minimize_window() -> Minimizes browser
    3. fullscreen_window() -> Makes browser fullscreen
    4. get_window_size() ->Returns window width and height
    5. get_window_position() -> Returns window position
    6. set_window_rect(x , y , width , height) -> Sets window size and position
    7. set_window_position(x , y) -> Moves window
    8. get_window_rect() -> Retuns window size and position

    Example:
        driver.maximize_window()
    driver.minimize_window()

8️⃣ Element Interaction Methods
Used to find and interact with elements on a webpage.
Common actions:
    1. Find element
    2. click
    3. Enter text
    4. Submit form

    Example:
        from selenium.webdriver.common.by import By
        search_box = driver.find_element(By.ID, "search-input")
        search_box.send_keys("Selenium Python")
        search_box.submit()

    Explanation:

        1. find_element() → finds element
        2. send_keys() → enters text
        3. submit() → submits form
    
9️⃣ Cookie Management Methods
Cookies store user session data.
Selenium allows us to manager cookies.
    Method & Description
    --------------------
    1. add_cookie() -> Adds cookie
    2. get_cookie() -> Get cookie by name 
    3. get_cookies()    -> Get all cookies
    4. delete_cookies() -> Delete cookie by name
    5. delete_all_cookies() -> Delete all cookies

    Example:
        driver.get_cookies()
        driver.delete_all_cookies()
    
🔟 JavaScript Execution Methods
These methods allows selenium to run javascript code inside the browser.
    Method & Description
    --------------------
    1. execute_script() -> Execute javascript synchrnously
    2. execute_async_script() -> Executes Javascript asynchronously

Example:
    driver.execute_script("alert('Hello Selenium')")

1️⃣1️⃣ Screenshot Methods
Used to capture screenshots of the webpage.
    Method & Description
    --------------------
    1. get_screenshot_as_file() -> Saves SC as PNG file
    2. get_screenshot_as_png() -> returns SC as binary data
    3. get_screenshot_as_base64() -> Returns SC as base64 string

    Example:
        driver.get_screenshot_as_file("page.png")
    
1️⃣2️⃣ Session & Page Information Methods
Used to get browser session and page details.
    Method & Description
    --------------------
    1. current_url -> Reutns current page URL
    2. title -> Returns page title
    3. page_source -> Returns HTML source
    4. current_window_handle -> Retuns current window handle
    5. quit() -> Closes all browser windows
    6. close() -> Closes current window

    Example:
        print(driver.title)
        print(driver.current_url)

        driver.close()
        driver.quit()

    Difference:
    close() → closes current window
    quit() → closes all browser windows

1️⃣3️⃣ Timeout Methods
Used to control waiting time in Selenium.
    Method & Description
    ---------------------
    1. implicitly_wait(seconds)	 -> Waits for element to appear
    2. set_script_timeout(seconds) -> Max time for async JavaScript

    Example:
        driver.implicitly_wait(10)

1️⃣4️⃣ Advanced Methods
Used for advanced automation.
    Method & Description
    --------------------
    1. create_web_element()	-> Creates WebElement manually
    2. get_log()	-> Gets browser logs

    Example:
        driver.get_log("browser")